<TITLE> UK-Bangladesh joint naval exercise ends </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 6 (bdnews24.com)The five-day UK-Bangladesh joint naval exercise dubbed 'Shomudro Torongo' off Kutubdia Island concluded on May 3, according to a British high commission press statement. The exercise aimed to share expertise to combat terrorism and preparedness for natural disasters in the region, the mission said in the statement on Wednesday. The Bangladesh Navy and the Royal Navy assembled their forces for a finale that saw them practising interception and boarding drills, according to the statement. High officials of Bangladesh armed forces and the British high commission attended the concluding part of the exercise. The highlights of the event included an air defence exercise, fire-fighting drills, ship manoeuvring serials and others. The statement quoted Commodore Peter Hudson, commander UK Amphibious Task Group, saying, "This ambitious and demanding exercise set some complex hurdles in a challenging coastal and riverine environment."
